  "texts": [
    "As for prompting strategies of fine-tuning LLaMA3-8B, we devise four prompts as follows:• Implicit prompting: it is the basic prompt used in our experiments as illustrated in Fig. 2(b).According to the rating threshold, we divide the items users interact with into likes and dislikes, and only provide the implicit feedback for LLMs as prompts.",
    "• Explicit prompting: compared to implicit prompting, explicit prompting does not divide items, and provides LLMs with explicit feedback of ratings scores.",
    "An example is provided in the third row of Table 14.",
    "• Hybrid implicit and explicit prompting: based on implicit prompting, hybrid prompting further adds ratings of the target user for each provided item.",
    "An example is provided in the fourth row of Table 14."
  ]
}